m leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"Deductions reduce taxable income before the tax rate is applied. A $5,000 deduction for someone in the 22% bracket reduces tax owed by $1,100. Pre-tax retirement contributions, mortgage interest, student loan interest, and business expenses are common deductions that lower taxable income."}]]}],["$","details","Is this calculator useful for quarterly estimated tax payments?",{"className":"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"cursor-pointer font-medium text-slate-900","children":"Is this calculator useful for quarterly estimated tax payments?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"Yes. For self-employed individuals or those with significant non-wage income, quarterly estimated payments are required. Use the calculator to estimate annual tax owed, divide by 4, and submit that amount each quarter to avoid underpayment penalties."}]]}],["$","details","Does this calculator account for multiple income sources?",{"className":"rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"cursor-pointer font-medium text-slate-900","children":"Does this calculator account for multiple income sources?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600","children":"Enter your total combined taxable income from all sources to get an overall estimate. For complex situations with multiple income types, different rates (capital gains, self-employment), or significant deductions, the calculator provides a useful baseline — but a tax professional can optimize the full picture."}]]}]]}]]}]
